<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Wound Staging adapted from Dr. Duggan's Geriatrics Guide</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Wound Care by Amanda Bailey, NP</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Document ALL wounds that are present on admission. This affects reimbursement.</span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Use the Haiku app on your cellphone to document images of wounds in pt chart</span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
